value.value: A question about which type of permanent cardioverter-defibrillator was implanted.

Historically, the term "aromatic" originally referred to the smell of selected compounds that later were found to contain benzene or fused benzene rings in the structure. In a structural sense, it designates compounds that, in accordance with the theory of Huckel, have a cyclic, delocalized (4n+2) pi-electron system. This includes arenes and their substitution products (e.g., benzene, naphthalene, toluene). The term has been generalized to include aromatic heterocyclic structures, such as thiophene and pyridine, but it is more precise to call compounds of the latter type heteroaromatic.

label.value: Coinfection of COVID-19 with Other Respiratory Infections

value.value: A respiratory infection that is diagnosed concurrently during an episode of acute illness caused by SARS-CoV-2.
Computed tomography of the chest.

label.value: Coronary Artery Aneurysm Related to COVID-19

value.value: Coronary artery aneurysm in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 0

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that no plaque or stenosis is present. Absence of coronary artery disease.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 1

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that minimal stenosis (1-24%) or plaque with no stenosis is present. Minimal non-obstructive coronary artery disease.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 2

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that mild stenosis (25-49%) is present. Mild non-obstructive coronary artery disease.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 3

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that moderate stenosis (50-69%) is present.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 4

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that severe stenosis (70-99%) or left main stenosis greater than or equal to 50% or 3-vessel obstructive (greater than or equal to 70%) disease is present.

label.value: Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score 5

value.value: A Coronary Artery Disease Reporting and Data System Coronary CT Angiography Score that indicates that total occlusion or subtotal occlusion is present.

label.value: Coronary Artery Ectasia Related to COVID-19

value.value: Coronary artery ectasia in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

The spread or migration of cancer cells from one part of the body (the organ in which it first appeared) to another. The secondary tumor contains cells that are like those in the original (primary) tumor.
A complication in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 that is not associated with a cardiovascular cause.
A new, discrete episode of acute COVID-19 in an individual with a prior history of probable/confirmed COVID-19.
An acute COVID-19 infection that is verified by detection of SARS-CoV-2 RNA in a clinical or autopsy specimen using a molecular amplification test (e.g., RT-PCR).
A likely acute COVID-19 infection as evidenced by detection of specific antibody in serum, plasma, or whole blood, or detection of specific antigen by immunocytochemistry in an autopsy specimen.

label.value: Acute Kidney Injury with Renal Replacement Therapy Related to COVID-19

value.value: Abrupt reduction in kidney function as measured by urine output and renal biomarkers requiring any renal replacement therapy in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Acute Kidney Injury without Renal Replacement Therapy Related to COVID-19

value.value: Abrupt reduction in kidney function as measured by urine output and renal biomarkers but not requiring any renal replacement therapy in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Acute Liver Injury with Fulminant Failure Related to COVID-19

value.value: Acute liver injury manifested by rapid loss of liver function associated with abnormal liver enzyme levels, coagulopathy or encephalopathy, and often multiorgan failure in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Acute Liver Injury without Fulminant Failure Related to COVID-19

value.value: Acute liver injury associated with abnormal liver chemistries (greater than two times the upper limit of normal) in the absence of signs of hepatic failure (e.g., no coagulopathy or encephalopathy) in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19. This is usually mild, transient, and does not require intervention.
Any subcellular process that results in a specific change in the primary sequence of a biological macromolecule.
The sudden or severe onset of neurological deficit(s) attributable to an acute focal vascular injury of the central nervous system in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
A dosing strategy that targets a standard treatment dose of an anticoagulant for the treatment of COVID-19.
A dosing strategy that targets a less than standard treatment dose but greater than a standard prophylactic dose of an anticoagulant for the treatment of COVID-19.
A data element that is used in the reporting of echocardiography.
A data element that is used in the reporting of electrocardiography.

label.value: Date of Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation for Cardiac Arrest

value.value: The date that cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) for cardiac arrest was performed.
The date that defibrillation was performed.
The date that direct current cardioversion was performed.
The date that the first COVID-19-related hospitalization occurred.

label.value: Date of First Hospitalization with Incidental Diagnosis of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: The date of the hospitalization when an incidental finding of SARS-CoV-2 infection was first diagnosed.
Cancer-causing genes encoded in viral genomes.  Usually denoted v-onc.
The date that the cardioverter-defibrillator was implanted.
The date that mechanical circulatory support was utilized.
The date that percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) was performed.
The date that SARS-CoV-2 booster vaccination was received.
The date that SARS-CoV-2 immunization was completed. In a vaccine series, this corresponds to the date of the last vaccination but does not include booster doses.

label.value: Date of Temporary Transvenous Pacing Wire Insertion

value.value: The date that the temporary transvenous pacing wire was inserted.
The date that SARS-CoV-2 testing resulted in a diagnosis.

label.value: Death due to Heart Failure Related to COVID-19

value.value: Death in association with clinically worsening symptoms or signs of heart failure regardless of etiology in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Death due to Pulmonary Embolus Related to COVID-19

value.value: Death as a consequence of pulmonary embolism in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Death due to Stroke Related to COVID-19

value.value: Death following a stroke that is either a direct consequence of the stroke or a complication of the stroke in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
Any event, process, or activity that produces a deleterious alteration of DNA. (NCI)

label.value: Deep Venous Thrombosis Associated with Post-Acute Sequelae of SARS-CoV-2 Infection

value.value: Formation of multiple thrombi in the large veins of the body, diagnosed with Doppler ultrasound, occurring most frequently in lower extremities or upper extremities, that started during probable or confirmed acute COVID-19 and persisted beyond four weeks after the initial diagnosis of COVID-19.

label.value: Deep Venous Thrombosis Related to COVID-19

value.value: Deep vein thrombosis in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.

label.value: Disseminated Intravascular Coagulation Related to COVID-19

value.value: Disseminated intravascular coagulation in a patient with probable or confirmed acute COVID-19.
Ultrasound examination of the blood flow through the vasculature of the lower extremities.

A biodegradable drug-eluting vascular stent that is coated with a polymer that releases an anti-proliferative drug to inhibit intimal growth and prevent restenosis after implantation. The polymer degrades after completion of drug release, leaving an inert metal scaffold in place.
